main event: Two witnesses, Mr. and Mrs. Leroy Wilkinson, observed three brightly lit objects with alternating red and green lights flying rapidly from south to north over Lewisburg, Ohio on March 21, 1965.
interesting points: The objects were estimated to be 35-40 degrees above the horizon and appeared to accelerate as they traveled northward.
The weather conditions were clear with good visibility, and no known aircraft were reported in the area at the time.
The investigator considered this a legitimate unidentified aerial phenomenon, as the witness seemed reliable and the description was consistent with other reported UFO sightings.
The report included 7 photographs of the rural landscape, but no photographs of the actual UFO sighting.
sighted object: three brightly lit objects with alternating red and green lights
photographs: yes, 7 photos of the rural landscape, but none of the UFO
